#: ../../../leds/leds-blinkm.rst:5
msgid "The leds-blinkm driver supports the devices of the BlinkM family."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../leds/leds-blinkm.rst:7
msgid ""
"They are RGB-LED modules driven by a (AT)tiny microcontroller and "
"communicate through I2C. The default address of these modules is 0x09 but "
"this can be changed through a command. By this you could daisy-chain up to "
"127 BlinkMs on an I2C bus."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../leds/leds-blinkm.rst:12
msgid ""
"The device accepts RGB and HSB color values through separate commands. Also "
"you can store blinking sequences as \"scripts\" in the controller and run "
"them. Also fading is an option."
msgstr ""

